headlines.description: — Bilal Coulibaly had 26 points, Corey Kispert scored 25 off the bench on five 3-pointers and the Washington Wizards handed the Charlotte Hornets their fifth straight loss 124-114 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coulibaly scores 26, Wizards overcome Bridges' first triple-double to beat Hornets 124-114

headlines.description: — Trae Young made a 23-foot fadeaway with 1.6 seconds left and scored 17 of his 34 points in the fourth quarter, lifting the Atlanta Hawks to a 132-130 win over the <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's fadeaway with 1.6 seconds left lifts Hawks to slump-busting 132-130 win over Pistons

events.name: Houston Rockets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 42 points and 10 assists, breaking a tie with Carmelo Anthony for third on the franchise list with his 18th 40-point game with the Knicks, and New York beat the Houston Rockets 124-118 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Brunson has 42 points and 10 assists to rally the Knicks past the Rockets, 124-118

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 33 points, and the Sacramento Kings edged the Minnesota Timberwolves 116-114 on Monday night after finalizing their trade for Zach LaVine.
headlines.shortLinkText: After dealing Fox, Kings eke out 116-114 road win over Timberwolves

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 34 points in 22 minutes, and the Oklahoma City Thunder routed the short-handed Milwaukee Bucks 125-96 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 34 as Thunder roll past short-handed Bucks 125-96

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 31 points, GG Jackson added a season-high 27, and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the San Antonio Spurs 128-109 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr., GG Jackson lead Grizzlies past Spurs 128-109 to hold second in West

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored a season-high 36 points, Nikola Jokic added 27 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Denver Nuggets overcame a career-high 41 points from Trey Murphy III to defeat the New Orleans Pelicans 125-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic's 23rd triple-double of the season leads Nuggets over Pelicans 125-113

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 10 of his 22 points in the fourth quarter to help the Indiana Pacers beat the Utah Jazz 112-111 on Monday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam's late surge leads Indiana to 112-111 comeback win over Utah

events.name: Orlando Magic at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 25 points and Stephen Curry added 24, leading the Golden State Warriors to a 104-99 win over the Orlando Magic on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins scores 25, Curry adds 24 as Warriors battle back to beat Magic 104-99

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 25 points and 20 rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers edged the Phoenix Suns 121-119 in overtime on Monday night for their fourth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton helps the Trail Blazers beat the Suns 121-119 for 4th straight win
